    "notes": [
      "Three-player JS oracle for a natural multi-step PrintManager gap, without seeded bodies or forced per-frame printing changes.",
      "p1 starts in a hole with an active PrintManager at exact-zero distance; the first tick toggles to printing and consumes tape value 0.0 for an 18-unit print distance.",
      "The next two 1000 ms ticks spend that print distance, emit normal trail bodies, then toggle p1 back into a hole at x=58 with tape value 0.5 for a 5.25-unit hole distance.",
      "On the third tick p1 toggles into a hole at x=58 using tape value 0.5, while p0 reaches x=66,y=40 inside that natural hole and stays alive.",
      "This fixture proves the newly created natural gap interior is body-free after a multi-step print cadence; it does not claim broader trail-gap, bonus, wall, or round-lifecycle fidelity."
    ]
  },
